		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1080,28,'With the \"Legacy of the Pharaohs\" exhibit in town, folks are crazy for faux-Egyptian trinkets. Pay $3 if you''d like to buy one, then make a <b>Luck (-1) check</b>. If you pass, it''s actually a real item! Draw 1 Exhibit Item or Unique Item.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (312,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (312,5)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (312,1081)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1081,21,'Although you adhere to the belief that hospital food should be avoided, your body demands sustenance. Gain 1 Stamina and search the Common Item deck for a \"Food\" card.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (312,1082)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1082,27,'A dog blazes past you, chasing a squirrel. Pass a <b>Speed (-2) check</b> or discard a Food card to take Duke''s Ally card, or, if it''s not available, $3 for returning him to his owner.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (312,1083)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1083,28,'Miriam Beecher thrusts a book into your hands. Taking a cursory glance through it, you notice that several pages are blank. She explains that a dark presence is erasing the knowledge it contains. Take a number of Clue tokens equal to six minus the number of elder sign tokens on the board.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (313,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (313,2)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (313,1084)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1084,21,'An old man who looks to be near death gestures you toward his bedside. If you approach, he tries to hand you something as his last breath gurgles out. Make a <b>Speed (-1) check</b>. If you pass, you catch the object; draw 1 Exhibit Item. If you fail, the ancient canopic jar shatters on the ground, and you are <i>Cursed</i>!')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (313,1085)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1085,27,'You find the rotting body of a foreign grifter that followed the museum exhibit into town. Pass a <b>Fight (-1) check</b> or become nauseous and move to the street. If you pass, you find his wallet and gun nearby. Gain $2 and you may search the Common Item deck for the .45 Automatic card and take it.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (313,1086)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1086,28,'A strange man roams the aisles looking desperately for something, muttering to himself. Make a <b>Speed (-1) check</b>, or he catches you watching him and attacks! Pass a <b>Fight (+0) check</b> to fend him off, or lose 1 Stamina.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (314,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (314,7)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (314,1087)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1087,21,'An orderly quickly closes the door to the morgue, but not before you catch a glimpse of what''s inside. Make a <b>Speed (-1) check</b> and gain 1 Clue token per success. ')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (314,1088)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1088,27,'You come across a cringing dog. Pass a <b>Sneak (-1) check</b> to catch him and calm him. If you have Food, you can discard that to automatically pass the check instead of rolling. You see by his collar that he is named <b>Duke</b>. Take his Ally card. If it isn''t available, gain $3 as a reward for returning him to his owner, instead.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (314,1089)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1089,28,'Upon discovering a severed - but twitching - hand, you find yourself trapped in an interminable time loop. You are <i>delayed</i>.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (315,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (315,5)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (315,1090)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1090,21,'As you walk through the halls of St. Mary''s, a nurse shoves a wheelchair into your legs, forcing you to sit. She wheels you recklessly through the hospital, informing you frequently that you will be \"good as new.\" Then, stopping abruptly, she tips you out of the chair and to the floor, and speeds off. Unbelievably, your Stamina is restored to full.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (315,1091)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1091,27,'As you trudge down a muddy path, a monster appears! If you kill it, take $5 (and the taxidermist''s thanks).')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (315,1092)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1092,28,'Customers in the store are gossiping about a recent strange occurrence, and who or what may have caused it. Turn the top card of a location of your choice faceup. The next investigator to have an encounter at that location draws that card.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (316,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (316,3)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (316,1093)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1093,21,'By quietly listening to the nurses talk, you are able to learn some useful information. Gain 1 Clue token.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (316,1094)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1094,27,'Hearing someone approach, you quickly climb a tree. It turns out to be several members of the Sheldon Gang. Nervously, you listen as they start talking directly under the tree you''re in. Pass a <b>Sneak (-2) check</b> to remain unnoticed and gain 2 Clue tokens. If you fail, they notice you and beat the tar out of you. Lose 2 Stamina.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (316,1095)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1095,28,'As you enter the Magick Shoppe, Miriam Beecher doesn''t even look up. \"Sorry, we''re closed right now. I''m performing a cleansing of the store. You''ll have to leave.\" Move to the street.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (317,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (317,3)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (317,1096)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1096,21,'Dr. Mortimore eyes you with suspicion. \"Excuse me, but who are you here to see?\" Pass a <b>Will (-1) check</b> to come up with a plausible excuse and remain here. If you fail, the Doctor has security escort you outside. Move to the street.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (317,1097)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1097,27,'Abruptly, you realize that you don''t remember how to get back out of the woods. Stay here next turn.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (317,1098)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1098,28,'Miriam looks into your face, and you feel as though you''re being judged. \"I see. Your heart is in the right place. Tell me of your travels, and perhaps I can help you in return.\" Gain 1 Clue token for every gate trophy you have.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (318,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (318,1)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (318,1099)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1099,21,'Make a <b>Luck (-1) check</b>. If you pass, you realize that Dr. Mortimore is sneaking up behind you with a hypodermic needle filled with a phosphorescent gel. You avoid his experiment and subdue the mad doctor. The city awards you $3 and you gain 2 Sanity in the process. If you fail, lose 2 Sanity, then you are dumped in the street.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (318,1100)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1100,27,'You are bushwhacked by the Sheldon Gang. Pass a <b>Luck (-1) check</b> to avoid their trap. If you fail, lose 2 items of your choice and 2 Stamina.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (318,1101)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1101,28,'You see an interesting book sitting open on Miriam Beecher''s desk. Pass a <b>Lore (-1) check</b> or you peer closely at its pages only to realize too late that the book is <i>Cursed</i>... and now, so are you.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (319,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (319,4)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (319,1102)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1102,21,'Nurse Sharon asks for your help in organizing some records that were accidentally dropped and scattered. Pass a <b>Lore (+0) check</b> to gain 1 Clue token.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (319,1103)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1103,27,'An easel and paints have been left here, abandoned by the artist. Not far away is the still life he was painting. Draw a card from the Common Item deck. If it is a <i><b>Weapon</b></i>, discard it. Otherwise, keep it.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (319,1104)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1104,28,'\"Ah, there you are. That item you ordered has come in.\" Oddly enough, you ordered no such item. If you wish, you may make a <b>Will (-2) check</b> to impersonate the rightful owner. If you pass, you may draw 1 Unique Item. If you fail, you are <i>arrested</i>.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (320,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (320,3)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (320,1105)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1105,21,'Nurse Sharon offers to bandage up your wounds. Gain 2 Stamina.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (320,1106)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1106,27,'You come across a cringing dog. Pass a <b>Speed (-2) check</b> to catch and calm him. If you have <i>Food</i>, you can discard that to automatically pass the check instead of rolling. You see by his collar that he is named <b>Duke</b>. Take his Ally card. If it isn''t available, gain $3 as a reward for returning him to his owner, instead.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (320,1107)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1107,28,'Miriam Beecher offers to teach you the spell you need. You may pay $5 to search the Spell deck and take any one card you want. If you turn down her offer, nothing happens.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (321,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (321,1)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (321,1108)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1108,21,'Nurse Sharon slips something into your hand when the doctor isn''t looking. Pass a <b>Sneak (-1) check</b> to keep anyone else from noticing. If you do, you later examine the object and find it to be an old parchment with a spell scratched on it. Draw 1 Spell. If you fail, an orderly takes it away from you and you gain nothing.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (321,1109)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1109,27,'You come across a cringing dog. Pass a <b>Speed (-2) check</b> to catch and calm him. If you have <i>Food</i>, you can discard that to automatically pass the check instead of rolling. You see by his collar that he is named <b>Duke</b>. Take his Ally card. If it isn''t available, gain $3 as a reward for returning him to his owner, instead.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (321,1110)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1110,28,'Miriam Beecher talks to you for awhile, explaining some very interesting theories she has concerning the Mythos. Gain 1 Clue token.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (322,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (322,3)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (322,1111)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1111,21,'One of the doctors tells you about an experimental treatment that might help you. It''s expensive, however. You may pay $5 to roll a die. On a success, discard one of your Injury cards. On a failure, gain 2 Stamina.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (322,1112)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1112,27,'Old Sadie Sheldon, leader of the Sheldon Gang, is here. \"Hmm. Do you think you have what it takes to join my gang?\" If you spend at least 5 toughness worth of monster trophies or 1 gate trophy, she accepts you into the gang. Take a <b>Sheldon Gang Membership</b> card. If you do not spend the trophies, she has her boys throw you out. Move to the street and lose 1 Stamina.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (322,1113)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1113,28,'Miriam Beecher offers to trade spells with you. You may discard 1 Spell to draw a new one from the Spell deck.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (323,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (323,3)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (323,1114)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1114,21,'One of the doctors tells you about an experimental treatment that might help you. It''s expensive, however. You may pay $5 to roll a die. On a success, discard one of your Injury cards. On a failure, gain 2 Stamina.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (323,1115)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1115,27,'A gate and a monster appear!')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (323,1116)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1116,28,'Miriam Beecher offers to teach you the spell you need. You may pay $5 to search the Spell deck and take any one card you want. If you turn down her offer, nothing happens.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (324,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (324,1)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (324,1117)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1117,21,'One of the staff physicians talks some sense into you. You are disabused of certain crazy but accurate notions. Lose 1 Clue token.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (324,1118)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1118,27,'You trip over an object which turns out to be a rusty lockbox. If you open it, make a <b>Luck (+0) check</b> and consult the following chart:<br /><br />Successes:<br />0) A rotted human foot. Lose 1 Sanity.<br />1) Draw 1 Common Item.<br />2) Draw 1 Unique Item.<br />3+) $10 in jewelry.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (324,1119)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1119,28,'Looking closely at a mummified head in the shop, you are horrified to find it looking back at you! Lose 1 Sanity.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (325,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (325,6)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (325,1120)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1120,21,'Someone has left a package unattended in the waiting room. Pass a <b>Luck (-2) check</b> to draw 1 Unique Item before the hospital staff finds it.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (325,1121)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1121,27,'You''ve stumbled upon the Cult of the Black Goat! You may join them if you wish. To do so, you must discard at least 2 toughness worth of monster trophies, lose 3 Stamina, or an Ally. Take a \"One of the Thousand\" Cult Membership card. If you cannot or choose not to join, pass a <b>Speed (-2) check</b> or lose 2 Stamina.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (325,1122)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1122,28,'Miriam Beecher offers to teach you the spell you need. You may pay $5 to search the Spell deck and take any one Spell you want. If you turn down her offer, nothing happens.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (326,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (326,3)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (326,1123)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1123,21,'The ambulance crew is heading home for the night and offers you a lift. Move to any street area or location in Arkham. If you choose to move to a location, immediately have an encounter there.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (326,1124)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1124,27,'Old Sadie Sheldon, leader of the Sheldon Gang, is here. \"Hmm. Do you think you have what it takes to join my gang?\" If you spend at least 5 toughness worth of monster trophies or 1 gate trophy, she accepts you into the gang. Take a <b>Sheldon Gang Membership</b> card. If you do not spend the trophies, she has her boys throw you out. Move to the street and lose 1 Stamina.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (326,1125)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1125,28,'Miriam Beecher looks up as you enter the shop. \"It''s about time you arrived. I have a job for you to do.\" Take the first <i><b>Mission</b></i> from the Unique Item deck.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (327,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (327,6)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (327,1126)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1126,21,'The cafeteria food, while tasteless, is quite nutritious. Gain 1 Stamina.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (327,1127)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1127,27,'The sound of chanting fills the night air, poisoning your soul. you may resist the effect by passing a <b>Will (-1) check</b>. If you fail, draw a Corruption card.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (327,1128)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1128,28,'A smiling man greets you warmly. \"It''s nice to see you again!\" You believe he has you mistaken for someone else, but he responds, \"Nonsense! I''ve been meaning to return this to you.\" He hands you a package and leaves. Gain 1 Common Item.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (328,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (328,1)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (328,1129)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1129,21,'The corpse you are examining isn''t quite dead yet. It reaches out and grabs you by the throat. Lose 1 Sanity. Then, you must fight the corpse. If you pass a <b>Combat (-1) check</b>, you defeat it and gain 1 Clue token. Otherwise, move to the street.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (328,1130)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1130,27,'You have stumbled on a still owned by the Sheldon Gang. Make a <b>Sneak (-1) check</b>. If you pass, skulk away without being seen. If you fail, lose 2 Stamina as the Sheldon Gang works you over while escorting you from the woods. In either case, move to the street.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (328,1131)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1131,28,'Looking into a glass ball, you receive a vision of things to come. Turn the top card of one location deck of your choice face up. The next investigator to have an encounter at that location draws that encounter card.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (329,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (329,1)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (329,1132)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1132,21,'The Doctor escorts you behind a curtain where the body of some other unfortunate investigator has been laid. The corpse has been torn to shreds. Pass a <b>Will (-1) check</b> or lose 1 Sanity. If you pass, you may also search the body and find a helpful item. Draw 1 Unique Item. If you fail, you run away screaming. Move to the street.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (329,1133)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1133,27,'A gate and a monster appear!')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (329,1134)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1134,28,'Pass a <b>Lore (-1) check</b> to recognize an item that Miriam Beecher has underpriced. If you do so, draw 1 Unique Item. You may purchase it for half its list price (rounded up).')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (330,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (330,8)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (330,1135)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1135,21,'The doctors insist on treating you! Ignoring any protests, they anesthetize you and start patching you up. When you come to, you''re physically fine but your thoughts are pretty foggy. Gain 2 Stamina but lose a Clue token if you have any.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (330,1136)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1136,27,'You notice an odd symbol carved into a tree. It leads you to another tree with a symbol carved into it. Make a <b>Lore (-1) check</b> to follow the path of symbols. If you pass, you discover it leads to an unusual object hidden under a rock. Gain 1 Unique Item. If you fail, lose 1 Stamina as you become increasingly exhausted.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (330,1137)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1137,28,'Speaking with Miriam Beecher, she tells you she would be willing to trade for items, if you have anything of interest. Look at the top card of the Unique Item deck. If you want to keep it, discard one of your Unique Items or Spells.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (331,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (331,4)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (331,1138)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1138,21,'The doctors know that something strange is going on, but don''t have time to talk. If you want to question them, you''ll need to look like you need medical aid. For each point of Stamina you are below you maximum, you may roll 1 die. Gain 1 Clue token for each success.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (331,1139)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1139,27,'Yellow-robed actors are re-enacting some sort of battle in the woods... or are they rehearsing for a battle yet to come? Pass a <b>Sneak (-1) check</b> to search the Common Item deck and take the first <i><b>Weapon</b></i> you find. If you fail, you are attacked and lose 2 Stamina.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (331,1140)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1140,28,'Behind a bookshelf, you hear a woman whisper, \"I have killed him I loved; the world''s athirst, now let it drink.\" When you look down that aisle, there''s no one there, but there is an item resting on the floor. Draw 1 Unique Item. You may purchase it for half list price (round up).')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (332,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (332,4)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (332,1141)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1141,21,'The hospital has a ward for special cases, but it is off-limits to the public. Make a <b>Sneak (-3) check</b> and gain 1 Clue token for each success you roll.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (332,1142)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1142,27,'You see a woman pouring blood on a field of flowers. When you move closer, she is gone. Make a <b>Luck (+1) check</b>. If you pass, she left her jewelry among the blood, and you gain $3. If you fail, the strange combination of blood and flowers is toxic and you lose 2 Stamina.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (332,1143)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1143,28,'No one is manning the shop, but an intriguing item is sitting on the counter. Draw 1 Unique Item. You may either discard it, keep it and pay its list price, or keep it without paying for it and be <i>Cursed</i>.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (333,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (333,2)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (333,1144)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1144,21,'The waiting room is filled with people complaining about a cough they''ve developed from a strange dust in the air. If you interview them, pass a <b>Fight (-1) check</b> to gain 2 Clue tokens. If you fail, you develop the cough yourself and can''t stay in the area without hacking and choking; you are <i>Barred from Uptown</i>.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (333,1145)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1145,27,'The Sheldon Gang needs someone to distribute the \"product\" from their hidden still. Make a <b>Sneak (-1) check</b>. If you fail, you are <i>arrested</i>. If you pass, you gain $3 and may search the Common Item deck for the Whiskey card and take it.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (333,1146)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1146,28,'As you wait in line to buy something, a swindler with scars on his face and a strange accent gives you a wink, then steps in front of you and begins to distract the shopkeeper. If you leave without paying, draw 1 Exhibit Item or Unique Item, but you are <i>Cursed</i>.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCard + " (334,9)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardExp + " (334,3)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (334,1147)");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertEnc + " (1147,21,'Tired, you sit down in a waiting room chair and accidentally doze off. When you awaken, you find out that several hours have passed. Stay here next turn.')");
		db.execSQL(sqlInsertCardEnc + " (334,1148)");
